@node "Document_1" " Introduction"

 Introduction


Congratulations for buying the programme DER_PROZESS_2.0 !

You have paid a  lot  of  money  for  this  produkt.  It  is  to  be  hoped,
DER_PROZESS_2.0  is  of  that  kind you have ever looked for, a tool staying
helpfully and comfortable at your side while engineering process-plants

The programming of DER_PROZESS_2.0 has taken  years  of  duration.  Starting
with  writing on an A1200 with 6 MB Ram and 40 MB harddrive, then further on
an A4000 with 10 MB Ram and two large harddrives.

The use of DER_PROZESS_2.0

The easiness of use is the key to our modern technologies.
It means, software should let work the computer for the user, and not the
user for the computer !

This is very important and ought to be permanent.

However, it is the wrong way, when the new programme you are  testing  seems
rather  to  be a stubborn creature that constantly refuses your instructions
than an usefull assistant. Possibly the programme is filled up  with  tools,
utilities and special instructions or you will find yourself into a dead end
from which the only escape is the Ctrl/A/A.

Not to speak of all the key-press connections you have to hold in mind.

During the programming of DER_PROZESS_2.0 the main thing in view was the use
of the programme. It has to be as easy and as simply as possible !

Almost everything can be achieved with both mouse keys

In case of finding yourself in a situation without exit, don't  panic  -read
at  first  carefully  the  manual. In deed with DER_PROZESS_2.0 it is almost
impossible to get in such an inescapable situation.

For what is DER_PROZESS_2.0

DER_PROZESS_2.0  is  for  everybody  who  has  to  do  with  pipes,   pumps,
heatexchangers,  vessels  etc. - i.e. the wide field of process engineering.
In DER_PROZESS_2.0 you will find a fast and simply to use assistant for  the
design  of  several  parts  in  plants  and the calculation of the different
dimensions like pressures, temperatures, diameters, amounts of flow, etc.

With the integrated funktion to simulate the displayed plant, you  have  the
possibility to observe the operation of a plant that still not exists ! I.e.
you have the possibility to study the behaviour of the plant without wasting
energie and materials.

These manual

The only purpose of the manual is to inform the user of the programme how to
work best with his programme.


I.e. if you find some repeats in this manual, dont worry. The reason is to
have a manual without the need to turn always over the pages.

However, don't be surprised about  the  shortness  of  this  manua.  On  the
strength of the easy of use of DER_PROZESS_2.0, it is not necessary to write
books over books of manuals.
@endnode

